### **4\. Byzantine Chain Bracelet**

The Byzantine pattern is one of the most intricate chain structures — featuring interlocking rings folded and linked in a complex arrangement that creates a flexible, textured, almost woven appearance. It has a distinctly ornate, historical character.

**Men's Byzantine — 7mm:** **[8" Men's Byzantine Chain Bracelet in 14K Yellow Gold (7mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/8-mens-byzantine-chain-bracelet-in-14k-yellow-gold-7-mm-item-150914?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — **$4,235**

**Heavy Byzantine — 5.25mm:** **[8" Byzantine Chain Bracelet in 14K Yellow Gold (5.25mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/8-byzantine-chain-bracelet-in-14k-yellow-gold-525-mm-item-147952?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — **$10,265**

**Largest Byzantine — 6.5mm:** **[8" Byzantine Chain Bracelet in 14K Yellow Gold (6.5mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/8-byzantine-chain-bracelet-in-14k-yellow-gold-65-mm-item-147953?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — **$13,230**

![8" Byzantine Chain Bracelet in 14k Yellow Gold (6.5 mm)](/images/822-Byzantine-Chain-Bracelet-in-14k-Yellow-Gold-6.5-mm.png)

**Important Byzantine pricing note:** The 5.25mm Byzantine at $10,265 costs more than the 7mm Men's Byzantine at $4,235 — despite being narrower. This is because the intricate Byzantine link pattern requires significantly more metal and craftsmanship per millimeter than simpler chain patterns. Byzantine chains are among the most labor-intensive to produce. The price reflects manufacturing complexity, not just width.

### **5\. Mariner Link Bracelet**

The mariner (or anchor) chain features oval links with a central bar running through each link — resembling the links of an anchor chain. It has a nautical heritage and a distinctly masculine, structural appearance.

**Standard mariner — 8mm:** **[8" Mariner Link Bracelet in 14K Yellow Gold (8mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/8-mariner-link-bracelet-in-14k-yellow-gold-8-mm-item-149059?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — **$3,935**

**Two-tone alternating mariner:** **[8.5" Men's High Polish Alternating Mariner Link Bracelet in 14K Italian White and Yellow Gold (6.6mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/85-mens-high-polish-alternating-mariner-link-bracelet-in-14k-italian-white-and-yellow-66-mm-gold-65-mm-item-193740?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — **$2,875** (was $3,195, −10%)

![8.5" Men's High Polish Alternating Mariner Link Bracelet in 14k Italian White and Yellow (6.6 mm) Gold (6.5 mm)](/images/8.522-Mens-High-Polish-Alternating-Mariner-Link-Bracelet-in-14k-Italian-White-and-Yellow-6.6-mm-Gold-6.5-mm.png)

The alternating white/yellow gold mariner is one of the most distinctive pieces in the catalog — the two-tone link pattern creates a visual rhythm that neither single-metal option achieves. The current 10% discount makes this the best value in the link bracelet category. Italian gold typically carries a slight premium for alloy purity consistency.

### **6\. Franco Chain Bracelet**

The Franco chain is a square-link chain where four links interlock in a V-pattern — creating a rope-like appearance but with a square cross-section. It is one of the sturdiest chain constructions available, resistant to kinking and tangling.

**[8.75" Men's Diamond Cut Square Franco Bracelet in 14K Yellow Gold (4.4mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/875-mens-diamond-cut-square-franco-bracelet-in-14k-yellow-gold-44-mm-item-192936?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — **$5,180**

![8.75" Men's Diamond Cut Square Franco Bracelet in 14k Yellow Gold (4.4 mm)](/images/8.7522-Mens-Diamond-Cut-Square-Franco-Bracelet-in-14k-Yellow-Gold-4.4-mm.png)

The extended 8.75" length makes this the longest chain bracelet in the standard catalog — appropriate for larger wrists or buyers who prefer a looser, lower-hanging fit. The diamond-cut faceting on the square links maximizes light reflection across the Franco's geometric surfaces.

### **7\. Wheat Chain Bracelet**

The wheat chain (also called spiga) features oval links angled at 45 degrees to the chain's axis, creating a herringbone-like braided appearance. It is one of the most flexible and comfortable chain patterns for daily wear.

**White gold wheat — 5mm:** **[8.5" Polished Wheat Chain Bracelet in 14K White Gold (5mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/85-polished-wheat-chain-bracelet-in-14k-white-gold-5mm-item-147977?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — **$2,165**

![8.5" Polished Wheat Chain Bracelet in 14k White Gold (5mm)](/images/8.522-Polished-Wheat-Chain-Bracelet-in-14k-White-Gold-5mm.png)

**Yellow gold wheat — 5mm:** **[8.5" Polished Wheat Chain Bracelet in 14K Yellow Gold (5mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/85-polished-wheat-chain-bracelet-in-14k-yellow-gold-5mm-item-147976?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** — **$2,165**

Identical prices for white and yellow gold at this width — one of the few places in the catalog where metal color does not affect price (at equivalent karat). The 8.5" length makes the wheat chain one of the most wrist-size inclusive options in the catalog.

## **Diamond Tennis Bracelets: The Complete 2026 Breakdown**

**Diamond tennis bracelets are the most technically complex men's bracelet category — and the one where understanding lab-grown vs. natural diamond pricing produces the most significant savings.**

### **What Is a Tennis Bracelet and Why Do Men Wear Them?**

A tennis bracelet is a flexible bracelet featuring a continuous line of diamonds (or other gemstones) set in a repeating prong or bezel configuration. The name comes from professional tennis player Chris Evert, who lost her diamond bracelet during the 1987 US Open and stopped play to find it — creating international attention for the style.

In 2026, men's tennis bracelets have become mainstream men's luxury jewelry — particularly in heavier carat weights (7ct–15ct) where the collective diamond presence reads as a bold wrist statement rather than delicate ornamentation. For diamond quality context, the **[diamond clarity chart](https://diamondcritics.com/diamond-clarity-chart/)** explains what the SI1-SI2 and VS2-SI1 clarity grades mean in practice.

### **Lab-Grown Diamond Tennis Bracelets: The Smart Buyer's Choice**

Blue Nile offers lab-grown diamond tennis bracelets in F-G color, VS2-SI1 clarity range — the same quality specifications used in their natural diamond equivalents, at dramatically lower prices. As documented in the **[lab-grown vs natural diamond price guide](https://diamondcritics.com/lab-grown-vs-natural-diamond-price/)**, lab-grown prices have collapsed 68% since 2020.

